##  Monitoring & Observability

### **Health Check Endpoint**

```bash
GET /api/health

Response:
{
  "status": "ok",
  "timestamp": "2026-03-08T14:30:00Z",
  "database": "connected",
  "redis": "connected",
  "queue_size": 5
}
```

### **Key Metrics to Monitor**

| Metric | Threshold | Alert If |
|--------|-----------|----------|
| **API Response Time** | <500ms | >1000ms |
| **Queue Size** | <100 jobs | >500 jobs |
| **Failed Jobs** | 0 | >10 in 1 hour |
| **Database Connections** | <80% | >90% |
| **Redis Memory** | <80% | >90% |
| **Disk Space** | <80% | >90% |

### **Logging**

```bash
# Application logs
tail -f storage/logs/laravel-$(date +%Y-%m-%d).log

# Nginx access
tail -f /var/log/nginx/access.log

# Nginx errors
tail -f /var/log/nginx/error.log

# Queue workers
sudo supervisorctl tail -f feepay-queue:* stdout
```

### **Telegram Alerts Setup**

Critical events auto-send to admin:
✅ Order success/fail  
✅ Digiflazz API errors  
✅ Queue job failures  
✅ Balance threshold alerts  
✅ System errors  

